title: Relates to reducing the fee for biennial registration for the professional practice of medical physics
summary: Reduces the fee for biennial registration for the professional practice of medical physics from $300 to $125.

S T A T E   O F   N E W   Y O R K
       ________________________________________________________________________

                                          252

                              2011-2012 Regular Sessions

                                 I N  A S S E M B L Y

                                      (PREFILED)

                                    January 5, 2011
                                      ___________

       Introduced by M. of A. CAHILL -- read once and referred to the Committee
         on Higher Education

       AN  ACT to amend the education law, in relation to biennial registration
         fees for the profession of medical physics

         THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK, REPRESENTED IN SENATE AND  ASSEM-
       BLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:

    1    Section  1.  Subdivision  6  of  section 8705 of the education law, as
    2  added by chapter 495 of the laws of 2001, is amended to read as follows:
    3    6. Fee: pay a fee of three  hundred  dollars  to  the  department  for
    4  admission  to a department conducted examination for licensure, a fee of
    5  one hundred fifty dollars for licensure with special competency  in  the
    6  first  specialty  and twenty-five dollars for each additional specialty,
    7  and a fee of [three hundred] ONE HUNDRED TWENTY-FIVE  dollars  for  each
    8  biennial registration period.
    9    S 2. This act shall take effect immediately.






        EXPLANATION--Matter in ITALICS (underscored) is new; matter in brackets
                             [ ] is old law to be omitted.
                                                                  LBD01051-01-1
